cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on self-supervised learning of convolutional neural networks for visual data, specifically addressing the ordering of visual data in the spatial and temporal domain. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of deep reinforcement learning to improve the sampling policy for permutations indicates a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The mention of transfer learning suggests a potential focus on robotics (cs.RO), and the use of convolutional neural networks suggests a potential focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
